trans-unit.resname: Jack Daniels' famous Running formula serves some tables estimating the VDOT value. These formulas are used to estimate your VDOT and predict your race performances.
trans-unit.source: Jack Daniels' famous Running formula serves some tables estimating the VDOT value. These formulas are used to estimate your VDOT and predict your race performances.
trans-unit.target: El libro de Jack Daniels “La Fórmula De Daniels Para Corredores” contiene tablas que permiten estimar el VDOT. Estas fórmulas se usan para estimar tu VDOT y predecir rendimiento es carrera.

trans-unit.resname: This table is computed by some formulas, derived from the tables in Jack Daniels' Running formula. These values do not fit the original table one hundred percent.
trans-unit.source: This table is computed by some formulas, derived from the tables in Jack Daniels' Running formula. These values do not fit the original table one hundred percent.
trans-unit.target: Esta tabla ha sido calculada con formulas derivadas desde el libro Jack Daniels' Running formula. Estos valores no son 100% compatibles con la tabla original.

trans-unit.resname: Values are visualized with so-called 'box plots'. They give an impression of how values of a group are distributed. The middle 50% of all values are within the box itself and the so-called whiskers have a length of at most 1.5-times the interquartile range (i.e. the box's width). Data points outside this range are called outliers.
trans-unit.source: Values are visualized with so-called 'box plots'. They give an impression of how values of a group are distributed. The middle 50% of all values are within the box itself and the so-called whiskers have a length of at most 1.5-times the interquartile range (i.e. the box's width). Data points outside this range are called outliers.
trans-unit.target: Los valores están visualizados con 'diagramas de caja'. Estos dan una idea de como están distribuidos los valores de un grupo. El 50% central de todos los valores está dentro de la misma caja y los 'bigotes' de las cajas tienen una longitud al menos 1.5 veces el rango intercuartil (o sea, el ancho de la caja). Los datos fuera de este rango se llaman atípicos.
